The paper discusses deep learning and generalization bounds for neural networks, which are topics commonly studied in the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), neural networks (cs.NE), computer vision (cs.CV), and systems and control (cs.SY). The paper specifically focuses on stochastic neural networks with many more parameters than training data, which is a common scenario in deep learning, further supporting the likelihood of these sub-categories.
